.TH "snd_ac97_reset" 9 "snd_ac97_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ac97_reset \- Reset AC'97 device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ac97_reset
.BI "(struct snd_ac97 *ac97 "  ","
.BI "bool try_warm "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ac97" 12
The AC'97 device to reset
.IP "try_warm" 12
Try a warm reset first
.IP "id" 12
Expected device vendor ID
.IP "id_mask" 12
Mask that is applied to the device ID before comparing to \fIid\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function resets the AC'97 device. If \fItry_warm\fP is true the function
first performs a warm reset. If the warm reset is successful the function
returns 1. Otherwise or if \fItry_warm\fP is false the function issues cold reset
followed by a warm reset. If this is successful the function returns 0,
otherwise a negative error code. If \fIid\fP is 0 any valid device ID will be
accepted, otherwise only the ID that matches \fIid\fP and \fIid_mask\fP is accepted.
